  body
    .page-wrapper.work-wrapper
      #work-banner
        include ../shared/nav.pug
        h1 FlipFlops
        span.sub-text Web & iOS
        img.banner-img(alt="banner image" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/banner.png")
      .work-details
        .detail
          p Role
          h3 Lead Designer
        .detail
          p Timeline
          h3 2 months
      p.work-summary FlipFlops goes where other food delivery apps won't... the beach. I got to design the mobile app for the customers, restaurants, and runners.
      .three-screens
        img(alt="flipflops example screen 1" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/example01.png")
        img(alt="flipflops example screen 2" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/example02.png")
        img(alt="flipflops example screen 3" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/example03.png")
      .user-types
        h2 User Types
        .user
          h3 Customers
          p People at the beach that are hungry but too busy or lazy to walk to nearby restaurants.
        .user
          h3 Restaurants
          p People that are receiving and processing orders from customers.
        .user
          h3 Runners
          p People that are taking the food from the restaurant to the customer.
      img.desktop-img(alt="flip flops example screen 4" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/example 04.png")
      .text-block
        h2 Flow charting
        p I typically like to start big projects with a flow chart. It helps everyone get on the same page and allows us to map out features and what will be on each screen.
      img.desktop-img(alt="flowcharting example" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/flowchart.png")
      .text-block
        h2 Design, prototype, build
        p I moved straight to design and prototype after building the master flow chart. I prefer designing and prototyping at the same time. This allows me to communicate more effectively with different members of the team during the design process.
        br
        p After a few weeks of design we started development of the iOS and web app. Unfortunately, the client was not willing to pay for user research time despite my best efforts.
      iframe.prototype(style='border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); border-radius:16px; box-shadow: 0px 2.56px 15.36px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.11);', src='https://www.figma.com/embed?embed_host=share&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.figma.com%2Fproto%2F24x9HzGcF25F0xxIlZi5m1%2FMobile-apps-portfolio-preso%3Fnode-id%3D54%253A529%26viewport%3D546%252C226%252C0.02175365947186947%26scaling%3Dcontain', allowfullscreen='')
      .text-block
        h2 Establish brand
        p I was lucky enough to work on the branding for FlipFlops. While this isn't what I typically the founders trusted me enough to work on a logo and color set for their brand. 
        br
        a(href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/na-roberts-638372141/" target="_blank") Logo by Na Roberts
      img(alt="" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/brand.png" style="width: 100%; max-width: 700px;")
      .text-block
        h2 Admin portal
        p The founders wanted an easy way to manage all the restaurants on the platform. They also wanted to give participating restaurants a way to manage their menus, payments, and business information. The admin portal makes it easy to do all that and more.
      .slide-controls
        svg.desktop-prev(width='38', height='29', viewbox='0 0 38 29', fill='none', xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg')
          path(d='M38 14.5L2 14.5M2 14.5L15 27.5M2 14.5L15 1.5', stroke='black', stroke-width='2')
        svg.desktop-next(width='38', height='29', viewbox='0 0 38 29', fill='none', xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg')
          path(d='M0 14.5H36M36 14.5L23 1.5M36 14.5L23 27.5', stroke='black', stroke-width='2')
      .desktop-slider
        .slide
          img(alt="admin portal example 1" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/adminexample02.png")
        .slide
          img(alt="admin portal example 2" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/adminexample03.png")
        .slide
          img(alt="admin portal example 3" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/adminexample01.png")
      .text-block
        h2 Restaurant app
        p We also created a separate app for restaurants and runners. The restaurant app allows restaurants to easily process orders and hand them off to runners.
        br
        p Once the order is turned over to the runner the app gives directions to the customers location on the beach. 
      .three-screens
        img(alt="restaurant app example 1" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/runner02.png")
        img(alt="restaurant app example 2" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/runner01.png")
        img(alt="restaurant app example 3" src="/assets/flipflops/desktop/runner03.png")
      #next-project
        #featured-work
          h2 Next project
          a(href="/mx-client-portal").work
            .left
              h3 MX Client Portal
              span.sub-text Lead designer / Web
              p Empowering MX's customers to manage thier most vital information.
              .view-project(href="/mx-client-portal") View project
                img(alt="" src="/assets/icons/arrow-right-red.svg")
            .right
              .featured-img(style="background-image: url('/assets/home/desktop/portal.png');")
